<p>Release tabs</p><p>The details for each release are found on the various CORDAP tabs.
	 
  </p> 
	 <p> 
		<p> CORDAP displays the
		  release-specific details on various tabs. Access these tabs from 
		  My Products, by expanding a product and selecting
		  a release. 
		 
		</p><p> 
		  <fig> 
			 Release tabs 
		   
		</fig> 
	 </p></p><p> 
		<p>General tab</p> 
		<p>On the General tab,
		  you can find the following sub-sections: Basic, Connections, Properties, and
		  Resources. 
		</p> 
		<p>On the General tab, you can find the following
		  sub-sections: Basic, Connections, Properties, and Resources. 
		</p>
		<p>On the General
		  tab, you can find the following sub-sections: Basic and Connections. 
		</p>
		<p>On the General tab, you can find the following
		  sub-sections: Basic and Connections. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		<ul> 
		   
			 Basics: set the product and
				release names and descriptions 
			  
		   
		   
			 Connections: create and save CMS
				connections 
			  
		   
		   
			 Properties: define the
				properties used to categorize product content 
			  
		   
		   
			 Resources: add users to the
				release 
			  
		   
		   
			 Properties: define the properties used to categorize product
				content 
			  
		   
		   
			 Resources: add users to the release 
			  
		   
		 
		</ul> 
	 </p></p><p> 
		<p>Features tab</p> 
		<p>You add all features for a release
		  on the Features tab. After you create a work package, you can link it to one of
		  the listed features. 
		</p> 
	  
	 </p><p> 
		<p>Assets tab</p> 
		<p> 
		   
			 <p>You must have a CMS connection
				to use this tab. 
			 </p> 
		   
		</p><p>You add all content impacted for
		  this release to the Assets tab. When a work package is created, the content
		  listed on the 
		  Assets tab is available to add to the work
		  package. If you add content to the work package, it appears as source content
		  in the work package. 
		 
		</p><p>Clicking an asset can show you
		  linked features, as well as the content of the asset in a read-only plain text
		  view. 
		</p>  
	 </p><p> 
		<p>Work Packages tab</p> 
		<p>All work package information is
		  stored on the Work Packages tab, but your view of this tab depends on your
		  role. Based on your role, you can see one of the following: 
		<ul> 
		   
			 Work packages assigned to you
				and all unassigned work packages 
			  
		   
		   
			 All work packages for the
				release 
			  
		   
		 
		</ul> 
	 </p></p><p> 
		<p>Iterations tab</p> 
		<p>The project leads can use the
		  Iterations tab to organize work packages into time frames called 
		  iterations. A brief summary of the progress made for the
		  iteration appears on the tab. 
		 
		</p><p>Based on your role, you can see one
		  of the following: 
		<ul> 
		   
			 Your progress for each iteration
				based on the work packages assigned to you 
			  
		   
		   
			 The progress for each iteration
				based on all created work packages 
			  
		   
		 
		</ul> 
	 </p></p><p> 
		<p>Change Drivers tab</p> 
		<p>Change drivers generated for the
		  release can be added to the Change Drivers tab. When a work package is created,
		  you can link it to a change driver. 
		</p> 
	  
  </p>